skos:Concept.skos:scopeNote: {"id": "a516bf05-71f6-4315-9959-821c9cedf3f8", "value": "A tool used to impart an image, impression or mark onto a surface."}
{"id": "b0a2c955-6abd-4971-ad9c-2fff28108aa9", "value": "A heated iron used to label, burn or mark animals, slaves, criminals etc."}

skos:ConceptScheme.dcterms:title: {"id": "d76b383a-4530-40a6-bb4e-56a1f44e181f", "value": "FISH Archaeological Objects Thesaurus"}
skos:ConceptScheme.dcterms:description: {"id": "ea9600cf-c6c6-40bf-9e62-0b28ede53667", "value": "Originally developed by the Archaeological Objects Working Party and published by the mda. It provides guidance for the recording of archaeological objects in Britain and Ireland covering all historical periods. Now maintained by FISH on behalf of the heritage sector"}

skos:Concept.skos:scopeNote: {"id": "8a15d2b7-dc2e-4fb5-a009-d3e602a06081", "value": "A graving tool used for engraving objects. Prehistoric versions are usually made of flint or other stone, later versions usually of metal."}
{"id": "dd840d62-035f-490d-9706-108de090e735", "value": "A hand held tool for marking or graving."}
{"id": "023d05c7-9c4f-4c78-8298-73738f37e306", "value": "A hard sharp point used to cut a design into metal."}
{"id": "cf775fc7-9d64-491a-9d83-d5c469c25f79", "value": "An engraved object which when struck imparts the image engraved onto the leather."}
{"id": "5afd8c50-ccc4-42a1-9a57-5675f98afacf", "value": "The object used to make impressions in wax as seals."}
{"id": "e9690d84-aa4c-4617-b6f8-a87fb7dcbc22", "value": "A tool for perforating or stamping, used in conjunction with a hammer."}
{"id": "98c8bbc0-932d-44fa-9ecf-3146e3a852f3", "value": "A tool used in etching which is the use of acid to breakdown parts of a metal plate in order to create an image."}
{"id": "7601c232-c2d5-4082-99f4-4ecc48ee0e84", "value": "A tool used to incise or ipress images."}
{"id": "7a27297d-3055-429d-a6d7-cfe5e7100484", "value": "Equipment used to create a mark, image or character in an object."}
{"id": "678f469b-b47c-4e75-99f3-7f20b2742cd0", "value": "A nail adapted so that the end of the nail can be turned over and driven back into the substance through which it has passed."}
{"id": "187bec97-5ce9-4cfb-9071-b3bc8e415a2d", "value": "A metal, stone or wooden projection with a flat upper surface to support a shelf, arch, statue etc."}
{"id": "9b88b961-83c5-4639-ab3f-9eded3301d05", "value": "A road vehicle designed to carry many passengers."}
{"id": "b52213ee-eee3-4015-b8a0-e3c2e2484f3e", "value": "A metal spur fitted to the leg of a fighting cock as an aid in fighting."}
{"id": "87685a7c-02df-468c-abd4-f70e10108fa4", "value": "A toy designed to exercise the ingenuity."}
{"id": "9f8016b9-f947-46a4-9a80-636ddfff9d11", "value": "A marker used to represent a gambling stake."}
{"id": "8457aaf5-eef5-4c3e-83a9-b3189bdb1478", "value": "Objects used or associated with sport and games, eg gaming piece. This class includes toys."}
{"id": "258a159d-6a3c-48f7-8e91-fab37f566ed4", "value": "A heavy disc, usually thrown."}
{"id": "f8b453e7-24c2-445a-b3a8-d454c576cff3", "value": "A small ball, usually of glass or porcelain, used in games."}
{"id": "768afabc-a45b-49ad-85e9-1e85ab43563b", "value": "A round object used in games."}
{"id": "891aaa5c-6746-408c-9ed8-c9d1eb358969", "value": "A board marked up to play a game upon."}
{"id": "ab5c64b8-e67c-4b5d-9b57-6543c6c80585", "value": "A peg or upright object which is the target of a ball in skittles."}
{"id": "87e7cf93-17a0-4cde-9b1c-919f5fafae5a", "value": "A gaming implement usually used in conjunction with a ball."}
{"id": "20c33be3-a213-4240-8ae0-f500e4c30ad9", "value": "An item designed to be played with by children."}
{"id": "2b8d3bd4-8aaf-4c84-a0ca-e3722be874ee", "value": "A flat, oblong gaming piece marked with spots used to play dominoes."}
{"id": "21cf4565-cb66-40b8-8228-0e1cee4d0aec", "value": "A marker used in the playing of a game."}
{"id": "f388fafa-8a07-484b-8325-98a51c2ea33e", "value": "A multi sided object usually used to obtain a unique value in games of chance."}
{"id": "e7863d18-d397-4d39-9277-316a97341f15", "value": "One of a pack, or deck, of cards used to play games, each distinguished from the others by markings on its face."}
{"id": "ffa27976-a86e-44ac-a1aa-040cb46d308e", "value": "A ring, often metal, which is used to be thrown as part of a game."}
{"id": "07195299-5fd4-4269-8e6d-4af47709d926", "value": "A container in which dice are shaken and from which dice are thrown."}
{"id": "bdca5764-c74a-4366-9540-c65e50fca1ff", "value": "Official currency printed or written onto paper which can be directly exchanged for goods, services or coins."}

{"id": "a697e3fb-3958-4850-be73-dcfeabe34f26", "value": "A jar whose profile resembles two truncated cones joined together at the widest point, forming a carination at the centre of the vessel. (Source: MPRG)"}

{"id": "b37b5837-888e-40cd-a527-37bbd65c1e59", "value": "A musket fired by a piece of burning match being held in the lock which, when the trigger was pulled, would contact with powder in the pan to set off the charge."}
{"id": "3bbb3d38-66f5-4964-a913-a0b1ed93d876", "value": "A heavy, smooth bore, long barrelled weapon, fired from the shoulder."}
{"id": "b126ab17-5ce4-4642-994e-db27eef28f52", "value": "A musket with a snaphance lock. This lock consisted of a flint and steel but the pan cover was separate to the steel unlike the flintlock."}

{"id": "e72f3470-82fc-48a7-ad5e-795e68043094", "value": "A musket where a wheel on the lock is wound back and when the trigger is pulled the wheel moves dragging pieces of iron pyrites over the lock tocreate sparks and set powder in the pan off and so firing the main charge."}

{"id": "28357b60-6e83-488d-b3dc-a84d02d5134b", "value": "A musket fired by use of a flintlock. A gunflint is held in the lock which on pulling the trigger pushes back the pan cover creating sparks which set off the powder in the pan causing a flame to go through and set off the charge in the barrel."}
{"id": "37744ce5-3519-4bd0-b235-4cb9e144c882", "value": "Clothes, items of attire and ornament and objects for personal use by individuals, including toiletries."}

{"id": "adef7dcb-2174-47a9-add8-291141c0a60a", "value": "A small, metal, crescent-shaped object, often highly decorated, worn across the upper part of the chest by military personnel as a badge of rank and as a symbolic representation of the former piece of armour (see also GORGET (ARMOUR))."}
{"id": "805ca8f3-62a1-4da9-a970-caae1260d9ca", "value": "An object belonging to, used by, or related exclusively to one person and normally carried or kept privately by that person."}
{"id": "40d88cd1-4270-45f9-977f-c636fe8ad0ea", "value": "Portable device that generate stable and consistent flame by combining flammable liquids or pressurised gases with a spark."}
{"id": "19b8f680-2d66-40d5-b64e-f9a4cb8c5a62", "value": "Items which are used in clothing but which are not necessarily a separate item of clothing."}

{"id": "43d5f140-b2bf-4470-9d7d-a9627099f69c", "value": "An object originally created to be worn on the human body or on clothing for ornamentation rather than for protection or as a body covering. Use only where the nature of the ornament is unknown otherwise use more specific term."}
{"id": "d9ab6645-5675-481e-8ff2-f18b647a0ad9", "value": "Covering and accessories worn on the body."}
{"id": "f6177cb5-4006-4351-855e-043062d1d1be", "value": "A container used to serve drinks and liquids."}
{"id": "64307965-3806-4a44-a6ca-3ce30f1200d4", "value": "Container with a handle, spout and narrow neck."}
{"id": "9c01039a-b0e1-4320-9751-daccb5352292", "value": "A stoppered bottle, for serving drinks."}
{"id": "3c59a27d-4d67-4e77-8e1d-325461dca0ae", "value": "A large jug, usually rounded with a narrow neck, used for holding liquids."}

{"id": "ba0e1f70-7940-4e9d-9274-55c672f5f982", "value": "A large vessel, sometimes large enough to accomodate several gallons, often made of leather and richly decorated, for storing and serving liquor."}
{"id": "4eaa34f0-24c2-442f-b59a-98c748c16c59", "value": "A container for holding or pouring liquids, usually having a handle or lip."}
{"id": "ce3f98a4-0ab8-40ae-b0b0-00f9599705ce", "value": "A container designed to assist in cooling foodstuffs or liquids. Use specific type where known."}
{"id": "5ad299e6-ca94-4a1a-9030-4fae67e33040", "value": "A small round dish on which a drinking vessel is set."}
{"id": "4dab7a45-eeef-4716-aa12-167134d2b2ad", "value": "A tool that produces a mark on an object through the application of percussive force through the stamp."}
{"id": "11155459-99e8-449d-9263-cb5c4848eab3", "value": "An object decorated or otherwise marked by the use of a stamp; for example, a maker's stamp."}
{"id": "d81aa034-7bc4-472a-bc63-0bc3fc9e6cb2", "value": "A material resulting from the smelting of iron ore."}
{"id": "8bc620b6-1b17-4002-83e0-08452042c98f", "value": "A horn used in hunting to give signals."}
{"id": "0de6f8c9-ecde-41c8-977b-76a8a13b606e", "value": "A war trumpet, usually Iron Age."}
{"id": "5bc3dc80-6a09-4b2b-97b9-c12cd0a50fea", "value": "An instrument which has a cupped mouthpiece and may have a straight, bent or curved tube. It includes slide trumpets like the trombone."}
{"id": "baa42090-6afd-4823-a82d-24913a67ba57", "value": "A trumpet type of instrument made from or in imitation of an animal horn."}
{"id": "bd5f758b-2c12-4a02-9509-2055c31e1298", "value": "An instrument in which air is made to vibrate by the player vibrating their lips and blowing into a mouthpiece."}
{"id": "97b387b6-f93d-431c-9d05-9cb4ace18ec8", "value": "A long tapered flexible pole used with a fishing line and usually with a fishing reel."}

{"id": "8a38e3a4-1034-4a43-ab4b-74ce6f782a89", "value": "A heating apparatus in which coals or embers are placed in the pedestal or base below a container in which food or liquid could be held and kept warm."}
{"id": "f21d15c5-93d9-42fb-97bf-100379d98731", "value": "A jar adapted by the addition of one or more handles. (Source: MPRG)"}

{"id": "404d356f-f510-4c58-ac92-9e88fdb98d20", "value": "A jar adapted by the addition of two handles. Handles may be horizontal or vertical loops or horizontal or curved lugs. Handles are nearly always opposed. Profiles vary and should be double indexed with the appropriate JAR type. (Source: MPRG)"}

{"id": "5f68187f-7bc1-4fba-810b-b4437bb57e58", "value": "A jar adapted by the addition of three or more vertical loop handles. They may be equally spaced, or confined to one section of the circumference. Profile vary and should be double indexed with the appropriate JAR type. (Source: MPRG)"}
{"id": "2d87c752-be42-444d-9bcc-597a94ef2117", "value": "A jar adapted by the addition of a single handle. Profiles vary and should be double indexed with the appropriate JAR type. (Source: MPRG)"}

{"id": "8f4d56eb-aa80-4170-81ce-a439b5a81996", "value": "A jar with a single handle attached to the rim edge and looped over the top of the vessel. There may be a lip. Profiles can vary and should be double indexed with the appropriate JAR type. (Source: MPRG)"}
{"id": "6b01b955-6f4f-451e-bde9-1ff320e6560f", "value": "A device for operating a lock."}
{"id": "abe2bbd0-04e8-4b4b-98b6-a09f97420263", "value": "T shaped piece of bronze imitating a key and hung from a chatelaine."}
{"id": "a61923ec-d93f-4f60-a048-94f476651871", "value": "A short chain or chains attached to a woman's belt for carrying keys etc."}
{"id": "8fc0f9b6-0440-4639-94d8-bb05368b7a97", "value": "Remains of any part of a hazel (Corylus avellana L.) nut."}
{"id": "7c18789b-3059-49c7-bda1-636474e9c8f3", "value": "A roll of paper or parchment, especially with writing upon it."}
{"id": "04604561-8201-4adf-9afd-e276297a04e4", "value": "A cloth or scarf worn over the head as a covering."}
{"id": "175e1b67-114d-4a42-941f-93ce3b17e9a2", "value": "A device with a sharpened surface used to grate objects such, as vegetables or cheese, into smaller pieces."}
{"id": "77008e2e-884a-462e-848f-81ae044bbb61", "value": "A mixture of lime, sand and water that is applied to the surface of a wall as a soft paste that hardens when dry. Often decorated."}
{"id": "aab9bd57-be62-4790-a742-b05187c6d1a9", "value": "A stud used for fastening an item usually used for clothing."}
{"id": "06c19a80-b7fa-44a3-9cd3-3ec0208abbb2", "value": "A vessel used as an ornament, often to hold flowers."}
{"id": "6d93d01c-0b38-4ee4-8417-513b46ce11f8", "value": "A vessel to contain the wafers used in the Eucharist."}
{"id": "7970df2f-cd9b-4078-9ac0-bbd89b426e0e", "value": "Cloth or leather covering for the leg or ankle."}
{"id": "3f893f82-1c25-4c06-84a8-55a1d6f5e1dc", "value": "A stone basin for containing holy water often set in inside walls of a church, especially near the entrance."}
{"id": "1c048d7e-cd78-481d-b4fc-221046345259", "value": "A hollow ball for containing aromatic substances eg perfume."}
{"id": "ae669985-8f44-493b-a1a3-d7ef730ddc2b", "value": "A set of shelves."}
{"id": "9f0cee52-46d6-41d7-bec9-37d7403dd204", "value": "A flat surface designed to hold objects. For a set of shelves use shelving."}
{"id": "81df4dd9-13bd-46c9-bfd5-b45c360d626f", "value": "An instrument made of a hollow cylinder or hemisphere covered at one or both ends and sounded by striking."}
{"id": "40d33097-1b4e-4c67-93f1-261166c52f96", "value": "A circular frame with a stretched membrane and small cymbals in the frame."}
{"id": "05dc5f23-1096-44bf-8aac-52842f92ca99", "value": "An instrument made by inserting a stick through a membrane stretched over a hollow vessel then played by rubbing the stick."}
{"id": "8583636b-47c5-413f-badd-865de3d4d998", "value": "A musical instrument producing sound from a membrane."}
{"id": "5efe10eb-0602-4ad1-838e-a37046960a32", "value": "A three dimensional representation usually done in wood, ivory or stone."}
{"id": "476bfed8-a27f-43de-941c-cdf4903c5c2c", "value": "A three dimensional representation of an object, person or animal."}
{"id": "1d5e3b6f-4aa4-41ce-865d-5425cffcfcb8", "value": "A small carved or sculpted figure."}
{"id": "21b84cd5-f558-4c2d-979f-d3e8cbf223a6", "value": "A three dimensional representation."}
{"id": "adefcd30-38e2-4585-bcf2-e75b3e92e733", "value": "A raised carving."}
{"id": "a6e48050-ba3f-41a9-b37a-5adddc83391d", "value": "The sculpted head, shoulders and breast of a person."}
{"id": "81b10ab2-ce93-440c-8739-411fa6a95882", "value": "A carved bust, figure or representation usually fixed to the bow of a ship."}
{"id": "7b29d9cd-a97c-4e2d-9a4f-aca45cb6057b", "value": "A decorative band or feature."}
{"id": "b08fac97-45d3-47e6-aac9-c2484ef8f4c2", "value": "A spout allowing water to spill away from a building. Usually carved in images of animals, people or grotesques."}
{"id": "50cf4684-be73-4b31-b292-cd1b2076322a", "value": "A wind-blown deposit."}
{"id": "f64cf787-55a7-491a-86d3-1d85cf84521e", "value": "Wind-blown sand."}
{"id": "188e8500-e032-4a47-b553-f7fba54bb19b", "value": "Wind-blown silt."}
{"id": "4650c72a-fadd-4cc1-a092-1b4c3df7ccb9", "value": "Remains of one of the groups of animals characterized as lacking any form of backbone or spinal column."}

{"id": "9be0817c-040d-41a2-9ab8-ede6fd7c75db", "value": "Remains of animals characterized as having bodies made up of annular segments, such as worms and leeches. Earthworm eggs and granule comonly occur. Bristle worms are found associated with marine molluscs."}

{"id": "548c107c-3892-4848-ae35-a14c4c534196", "value": "Remains of parasitic or free-living worms of the phylum Nematoda, characterized as having slender, cylindrical unsegmented bodies. Cysts of Heterodera commonly occur archaeologically."}

{"id": "c3d60661-6c35-462e-83dc-c7d832dc0b98", "value": "Remains of the animal group characterized by having jointed limbs and segmented bodies, including woodlice, spiders, insects etc. Note, crustaceans have been included in this category."}
{"id": "d17916ec-bb6d-4d08-bd02-c19c5ef28bf5", "value": "Remains of Bryozoa, which are small animals, usually marine, that form colonies producing coral-like skeletons or jelly-like masses."}
{"id": "74b41db8-cfc1-4026-8a9a-22843cdc00bb", "value": "Remains of the group of animals characterized as being radially symmetrical in form, such as sea urchins, sea cucumbers and starfish."}
{"id": "d443c242-16cb-4986-bb3b-f93582498df0", "value": "Use for the remains of any part of a mollusc. Use more specific term if known."}
{"id": "6dc264ad-9200-4bbe-a7dd-df21fdceb41e", "value": "An instrument in the form of a pair of pincers used to grip and pull objects, usually used in surgery."}
{"id": "a1bbd7cf-4bca-4126-b0ae-3cd660b41e38", "value": "A by-product of the production of microliths."}
{"id": "b03bdaf8-f41a-4aaf-b2c7-b27b268b700f", "value": "A shallow, usually circular, dish on which food is served or eaten from."}
{"id": "7975b78a-f719-45a7-b8cc-a4d1a339af15", "value": "A metal bar to strengthen the heel and or sole of a piece of footwear."}
{"id": "b77657ac-d3fa-406c-8eaf-60cb424afb9c", "value": "Any form of fastener used to fasten a cloak together."}
{"id": "c298932c-518d-4265-ae51-5d68c32d425e", "value": "An object which supports or is attached to a curtain."}
{"id": "25345a2b-98ea-49fd-8583-82e012bb3539", "value": "A pick with a point at one end and a cutting blade at the other end."}
{"id": "56e7c2d5-db88-45fe-87c4-628cea4d1222", "value": "A tool with a pointed head for breaking ground."}
{"id": "0df8d8ab-5a47-45cf-90ca-22135c4c0496", "value": "A wooden hammer."}
{"id": "66892c97-dded-45ee-9e71-0f52880b0269", "value": "Equipment used primarily to bring percussive force onto an object."}
{"id": "497b6476-4f26-4404-9355-28ed4bdcbf3e", "value": "A massive hammer of wood, stone or iron."}
{"id": "cc7ca0d3-af61-4891-9584-87ba9e1080e3", "value": "A tool used for digging where the blade is at right angles to the handle."}
{"id": "3a2aa9bb-abae-4976-a61e-df29d6b248ae", "value": "A blunt headed instrument used for striking objects."}
{"id": "17ae2b59-ced8-4344-9c25-88f8b1011d7d", "value": "A long handled heavy hammer used by two hands."}
{"id": "bf8bac48-b300-4240-832d-abec9ac86bb6", "value": "A general tool used to beat objects with."}
{"id": "ab948e6c-4ec1-48b1-a798-de932895cd25", "value": "A shaft hole adze with additional hammer knob, normally polished stone."}
{"id": "a366d0fb-effd-475e-9dd1-81d6e0a6bc8b", "value": "An axe with a cutting edge and a hammer head."}
{"id": "6350a2d9-cac5-4dcb-84a0-e0a7a7cd5579", "value": "A tool for threshing grain."}
{"id": "91868d44-07b4-494b-a004-1b0dbd4cb8bb", "value": "An partly-worked millstone that is still to be finished."}
{"id": "32a53a50-6ff9-4a53-a2ce-b509ce347592", "value": "Deposits formed by the mass downward movement of surface deposits over underlying frozen ground under periglacial conditions."}
{"id": "e6045ed5-0559-4d05-a6e0-eb013eadce57", "value": "Deposits formed under conditions present adjacent to ice masses during glacial periods."}
{"id": "0172d26e-1c7a-44a6-8133-3e8a469a070c", "value": "Storage vessel, usually a two handled narrow necked jar."}
{"id": "3f56e395-89c2-4281-a44f-549866a20de2", "value": "A metal container for liquids and foodstuffs, often sealed."}
{"id": "284f8163-2085-4c75-a5d9-086c4e383c24", "value": "A large container for milk."}
{"id": "cc51f2b7-f88c-43a6-abfa-90925f5ca065", "value": "A portable medieval container usually cylindrical or barrel shaped."}
{"id": "4dab66b0-9aef-4c35-b10b-eece32a2a30e", "value": "Container with arched handle used for carrying liquids, foodstuffs etc."}
{"id": "273ba38d-5201-4f08-ab44-5d17bac327db", "value": "A small earthenware container used for liquids."}
{"id": "8b56484f-e570-4032-8302-d2021a7b3c64", "value": "A flexible container, usually leather, for the storage and transportation of wine."}
{"id": "3165469c-1250-41bd-8eba-a7e711d45f25", "value": "A container, usually round and deep."}
{"id": "159b3b23-158c-4d81-a74f-0a8fae0c6fdc", "value": "A low, wide, open container."}
{"id": "24b2959e-f43a-4ca1-8a90-5f552897b7b1", "value": "A wide mouthed container, usually cylindrical without handles."}
{"id": "631c1431-e7c4-43bd-86ef-ab6973f5e239", "value": "A container for the storage and/or transport of food and/or liquid."}
{"id": "51f0bbb6-25ff-424f-88c0-b86d3dfb8689", "value": "A bottle with a narrow neck used for wine oil etc."}
{"id": "0a8f8b4f-c786-4bd4-8ebf-37fbd2ec515b", "value": "A large container or reservoir for liquids or gases."}
{"id": "c69d2b35-bf9b-411a-a2ca-ed79afe642a1", "value": "A large bag made of coarse cloth or thick paper."}
{"id": "5fe83822-c78a-4e5e-b0f5-10b89e0944dc", "value": "A large jug or pitcher with a wide mouth."}
{"id": "9f124253-06fa-4979-9aa3-4c0256b091cf", "value": "A large container for holding or storing liquids."}
{"id": "858165eb-ee77-4e07-94eb-b4b5a18cc0fb", "value": "A cylindrical container, usually bulging outward in the middle and usually held together by metal hoops."}
{"id": "9d6939ba-6217-45a4-a707-dbd6f49d4111", "value": "A container made of interwoven strips of pliable materials, such as cane or reed, often carried by a handle."}
{"id": "8b2bed06-b73b-4eef-a67f-8b326dd45471", "value": "A small barrel."}

{"id": "ccd16a0e-4914-471b-8109-2846952057aa", "value": "A two-piece Bow Brooch, derived from the Colchester Brooch, dating from the later first and second centuries AD and so called due to the decorative stud on the upper bow."}

Frequently tinned to give a silver appearance."}

{"id": "628a133e-b63c-4cf3-a554-a13646959e95", "value": "Any brooch with the pin sprung or hinged at one end and the catchplate at the other end of a curved or flat bow. Can be one or two piece construction."}

{"id": "bc40b694-af89-45a7-a314-ced2b95bae8c", "value": "A two-piece Bow Brooch dating from the early to mid-first century AD in Britain, originating in Gaul. {"id": "3898c38a-5cf6-468c-818c-a4c8fca9d9fb", "value": "Imported Roman brooch with a wide, highly arched flat backed bow, one end rolled forward onto the head to form a hinge for the the pin. Named for the head inscription assumed to be a maker's name. Dated to first half of 1st entury AD."}

{"id": "d9232783-3b22-4739-977e-3f4447075e92", "value": "Roman, mid-1st century AD two-piece Bow Brooch, derived from the Colchester Brooch, with a winged, transverse head protecting a spring mechanism held by a rear facing hook over the chord, its profile evoking a leaping dolphin."}

{"id": "80297f23-7ccc-4a00-9cdd-0e66d6c46087", "value": "Anglo-Saxon two-piece bow brooch, dating from the 8th to 9th centuries AD, so named for the distinctive bow shaped like the arching body of a caterpillar."}

{"id": "b049001b-7a40-4127-afea-e7f5a81d8c5f", "value": "A Roman brooch dating from approximately 50 to 150 AD. Derived from the earlier Aesica Brooch, and fitted with a hinged pin, the body widens to a triangular plate below the bow."}

{"id": "72bfe6d7-92ef-45d6-b1a4-5ef18cc27a18", "value": "A first century AD one-piece bow brooch, one end of which is drawn out to form a spring and pin, characterized by its long, narrow, tapering bow, a small crossbar in front of the spring and a forward hook which holds the spring chord."}

{"id": "824ddb29-50a5-4551-b97d-1b3401676068", "value": "Early to mid-1st century AD Bow Brooch with a P-shaped profile, a cylindrical or semi-cylindrical spring cover and a round or lozenge-shaped centre plate with a short bow above and a flat leg below, both of which are reeded like the Langton Down Brooch."}

{"id": "ff6adbc3-f659-447c-9bf1-03d9c8e027e0", "value": "1st or 2nd century Bow Brooch derived from the Colchester. It typically has a pin hinged on a bar held in a cylindrical crossbar, the bow tapering and commonly decorated. Developed examples often have a headloop and enamelled panels."}

{"id": "3d76bd29-47bb-4627-9bec-c9d355087967", "value": "Algae usually found as a silica skeleton. They obtain their food by photosynthesis and are used in ecological reconstruction."}

{"id": "6f21522b-ebc0-4cfa-939c-f7a9c838729b", "value": "Animal, vegetable and mineral remains including edible materials, drink or residues and unworked imported objects which have been retrieved from archaeological contexts. Also soil samples taken for environmental analysis."}
{"id": "80b867a1-05b0-4885-b291-1ed4719b120c", "value": "Use for the remains of any part of a plant."}
{"id": "d851ff5d-a516-4bfc-a254-b9d2422bbee8", "value": "Microscopic living things, usually unicellular, occasionally multi-cellular. They lack cell nuclei."}
{"id": "9ed390dd-1dc4-4a01-b08b-0f2df4102aa5", "value": "A specimen of material to represent the whole from which the sample was taken."}
{"id": "cd002a69-c888-4315-b5d1-c496b1577f5d", "value": "A stone used for sharpening edged tools, knives etc."}
{"id": "0db8e0f4-6358-452d-8689-6b74c8197e81", "value": "Remains of wheat (Triticum sp.) grain (caryopyses). These grains are sometimes itemised separately."}
{"id": "681d1190-d312-4cf7-a6bd-7b7064822be1", "value": "The fruit or seed of a cereal plant such as wheat, corn etc."}
{"id": "f4a0ef8c-7d47-4316-89cb-cef4d6d9d550", "value": "A container used to assist in cooling water."}
{"id": "4590f44a-ed43-49c5-b5d5-11f96cca5938", "value": "A piece of iron cut from blooms and lengths of bar, probably for transportation, which were then reworked."}

{"id": "e9d9147d-b1ef-49ba-9710-291e713adffa", "value": "Low-grade cast iron in the form of balls or spheres, produced in small workshops and exported across the North Sea and Baltic region. Particularly associated with 16th century Sweden. Also spelt \"oszemundt\" and other variants."}
{"id": "2509a055-c5f5-44e7-bca3-689fb36818e7", "value": "A tent especially one made of bark, rushes or skins spread over a set of arched poles that are lashed together."}

{"id": "76ae3153-9de1-4fca-944a-0e31aa8877cc", "value": "A coin which has been struck in relief on one side, usually the obverse side face down on the anvil die, and incuse on the other side, due to a previously struck coin sticking to the upper or punch die."}

{"id": "b1981158-1c4d-45e5-b8b6-d7aef112fa8b", "value": "A tool with an edged head and a wooden shaft, used for a variety of purposes. Where the function is known use the more specific terms of AXE (TOOL) or AXE (WEAPON)."}
{"id": "332190eb-d6b9-4ab9-9b72-41cdedf7bec0", "value": "A specially designed chisel for producing ornamental mouldings."}
{"id": "68f0e77f-b8db-40f5-9082-f60e08909f0a", "value": "A tube through which missiles are blown."}
{"id": "a2e7a314-096a-4c77-991f-aff12afc9511", "value": "A pot for drinking hot milk curdled with ale and flavoured with spice used as a remedy eg for colds."}

{"id": "3e2eb539-074b-460d-9b11-a84d750153c7", "value": "In the glass industry, material spilled or raked from the top of the crucible during melting: important for assessing the methods of glass-making, and a common find on furnace sites. Roman period onwards"}
{"id": "aac8e8a4-94e2-4f17-8c3f-7cc6c5c2c50e", "value": "A container for the storage of rice."}
{"id": "c786c4bc-a719-4caf-aa98-c63cf07777c6", "value": "A small bobbin used in lace making."}
{"id": "4df5e0d7-d6f9-4c0a-98f3-1ad9e86a3c49", "value": "A structure consecrated for devotional purposes."}
{"id": "34a215db-a861-4498-a8c5-0e13e53c1182", "value": "A box used for storage or shipping."}
{"id": "e90565f0-ad6d-4de9-83ec-a4d188cd836a", "value": "Material hung from walls, excluding paper."}
{"id": "dd2c7356-0fd8-4acd-b835-90ab1163863d", "value": "Large wall hung tapestries only."}
{"id": "5a81f94c-747e-4be3-8a29-76db1ecf4fea", "value": "A by-product created during the manufacture of a tool."}
{"id": "99c843b7-deda-441d-9dcd-24d258f034e0", "value": "Any by-product which cannot be reused."}
{"id": "ec68732d-c3f8-4309-a56f-5ac543be7129", "value": "A secondary or incidental product of a process."}
{"id": "23d26d33-7fc8-4a32-b546-201ec1ad723f", "value": "An object that has been cut off."}
{"id": "4e606bfc-6902-4109-91ec-eb2a57a3c17e", "value": "A collective name for the pans and fire bars used in the making of salt through evaporation."}

{"id": "1c1e8e77-c06e-4ef3-8bb6-82120268d58c", "value": "Glass fragments collected for re-melting. This includes not only worked fragments, but pieces broken from blowing irons and pontils, (moyles). All periods from the Roman onwards."}
{"id": "3d93f203-84ca-4cd0-87b7-e1889176dede", "value": "Part of the glass making process, the frit is broken up into a crucible and heated to create glass."}
{"id": "2364c7e7-e8c9-4a3e-b502-a3e2a5778669", "value": "A short hooded cloak."}

{"id": "c7102d9a-d78b-4b76-b0ab-fa86c1676bd0", "value": "A plucked string instrument of a specific medieval / early post medieval type."}

{"id": "2b36d896-5f8c-4bf4-b991-93d8c87987cd", "value": "A seat of state, often highly decorative, used by monarchs, bishops, etc."}

{"id": "afc87ffd-e21e-481b-9dd3-8e417982c994", "value": "An item hung over a window, usually can be open or shut to allow light in."}
{"id": "3f190fbf-f097-46cb-8972-0b206f00d4c4", "value": "Bag filled with soft stuffing used to support the body."}

{"id": "b5a303ba-59ac-4ef6-974f-4c46460842f1", "value": "A tray used for separating the grain from husks and straw."}
{"id": "23d4295f-4f84-44a2-afa7-60b53f862f80", "value": "A form of dagger."}
{"id": "65892bee-8064-40e0-b565-24e63aa6db0f", "value": "A staff with a bent head used by a shepherd. For a crook used by a bishop use crozier."}
{"id": "bf68d206-73b4-40ee-b01c-f27027528e8d", "value": "Characteristic waste flakes struck off in the production of axes."}
{"id": "aff63a44-1da2-47df-b3a3-1c508819dd34", "value": "A weapon which causes damage through exploding."}
{"id": "2a2f14de-09db-4cb1-8267-1fcb8cc5a464", "value": "A small explosive device, usually hand thrown."}

{"id": "7db0be5d-d5db-40d5-8913-12d6fdd60694", "value": "A container packed with explosives, with a detonator triggered by contact or a timer, for the purpose of destroying enemy craft, personnel etc."}

{"id": "615670bf-3cb5-4371-93c9-97c6b425ba7c", "value": "Derived from the Colchester in the mid to late 1st century, particularly in south and east Britain. Characterized by the attachment of the separate spring and pin through two holes in a lug behind the head, which projects to form a crest atop the bow."}
{"id": "85e1ed52-b23c-4c64-94ec-d73d13120962", "value": "A pouch for containing tobacco."}

{"id": "5cb37ac6-2918-4769-b698-b2b28defb65e", "value": "A large one handled drinking vessel, sometimes fitted with a hinged lid."}
{"id": "735fa771-ee8b-4f2c-9897-a30fa7b330c7", "value": "A vessel with a specially adapted mouthpiece, to assist in feeding young animals and humans."}

{"id": "15aa7391-faf5-4aec-abd7-6481a819e151", "value": "A term for a drinking vessel, although its use often implies a recognised quantity."}
{"id": "9a734d89-b1c5-4c50-b472-1b501f9721ee", "value": "A portable beehive, often made of straw."}
{"id": "85b15553-78ec-4f5c-8465-2e08dabd8e68", "value": "A receptacle used as a home for bees, traditionally made of thick straw work in the shape of a dome,but sometimes made of wood."}
{"id": "5bb40991-efaa-402d-aa78-ca06d59288a7", "value": "A jug with more or less straight sides that flare out from a narrow rim or neck to a wider base. (Source: MPRG)"}
{"id": "0443e495-2696-4a1b-9316-0cae220b9054", "value": "Scissor like object used for cutting, clipping, shearing etc."}
{"id": "199ed2ca-753d-4a7b-ab4f-39e6b5ff0fdc", "value": "A flat nail of the same thickness that tapers in width to a point."}
{"id": "1c851050-e423-436c-b071-ae3079ca5068", "value": "A nail used for roofing."}
{"id": "0046f1d7-7720-4be8-bd41-83678f11599d", "value": "A metal spike for fixing one object to another."}
{"id": "07b5787a-86d1-4d43-9980-267c5426be68", "value": "Short-range naval weapon with a low muzzle velocity"}

{"id": "ae030159-52cb-4d9f-b6e2-ed6a5873febb", "value": "Remains of arthropods characterized as having a body divided into two segements and four pairs of legs, such as spiders, scorpions, ticks and mites."}

{"id": "dcf7f37a-d256-4f04-8694-46027ddff4b3", "value": "Use for ticks and true mites. Related to spiders, mites are widely present in archaeological deposits but are rarely studies in detail as they can prove difficult to identify."}
{"id": "b5c44b28-6f7f-4cf8-8d66-8a58a06802c5", "value": "A block of metal with a device cut into it, used to impress a coin blank."}
{"id": "09e66c21-badb-4227-8c3e-3baf8902ad60", "value": "A round container, open and wide at the top with sides sloping inwards toward the bottom."}

{"id": "f087c2be-7407-4846-932e-7f7b59494b10", "value": "Any object, often made of ceramic or 'porcelain'used for the purposes of personal cleansing, especially fittings such as toilets, baths and basins. May survive as fragments in the archaeological record. Use more specific term where known."}
{"id": "b9244cdf-2dbc-407e-8e57-d5a5013a9bae", "value": "A large container used for washing the body."}
{"id": "7119b0cf-d272-429c-8552-a0427ee5aa1d", "value": "The remains of the fine powdery substance produced by male elements of flowering plants, uniquely identifiable to the species it came from."}
{"id": "65cbb5ff-8956-49a6-ace1-0571a87d5d93", "value": "A ring, flange or short piece of pipe, made of iron, clay or other materials, used to join and seal two sections of water pipe."}
{"id": "d11b881f-67bb-4872-86cf-25ced34cb386", "value": "A fitting of unknown function. Use more specific type where known."}
{"id": "133dd339-d095-4f59-b569-a4848c7e1988", "value": "A Mesolithic type of mace head made of stone."}

{"id": "cbe76c72-11d1-4ada-bb22-b73a3fdaeea2", "value": "A type of mace with bolster shaped stone or metal head on a wooden or metal shaft. Where the use is thought to be ceremonial, double index with ceremonial object."}
{"id": "2a075311-7d8d-4daa-81db-e0b6bb2e2c22", "value": "A stone or metal head on a wooden shaft. Where the use is thought to be ceremonial multiple index with ceremonial object."}
{"id": "7391e645-8e83-4247-8c5a-e86ae4e48f94", "value": "A tool with a sharp, concave edge for shaping wood, stone or metal."}
{"id": "c84e85c4-3733-4ca3-9630-8f6c23942c70", "value": "A type of cast chisel with a sharp, concave edge for shaping wood, stone or metal. A particular type of British Bronze Age tool."}

{"id": "96050882-f736-4c4c-8309-958bff9c1958", "value": "A jug that incorporates a practical joke or conundrum into its construction. A combination of cut-outs in the body and hollow handles and tubes render conventional use impossible. The puzzle being to work out how to empty it. (Source: MPRG)"}
{"id": "894339c7-5e82-41e1-a996-b7f538120c63", "value": "A bowl for the washing of hands, often in a religious institution."}
{"id": "54974d2f-bde4-4957-b015-9fb1174ddf33", "value": "A bowl for the ritual washing of hands."}
{"id": "c2b76348-c3c1-4002-9061-1fa59bef02f1", "value": "An object designed to float in water and to support a net."}
{"id": "a410435f-e800-45ab-8edd-418bbad311b2", "value": "An object that supports another in water, eg float on a fishing line or net."}

{"id": "3c63d09a-e50b-42a4-bd35-59166c5713b9", "value": "A stone core with a conical form and a core platform which may or may not be prepared. Blades are removed around the circumference of the platform. The end of the core opposite the platform usually tapers to a point. (Source: SARC)"}
{"id": "1a3893f8-9ee4-4b87-bc6a-47f2375576c5", "value": "A saucerlike vessel of earthenware or metal, used by the Greeks and Romans in libations and sacrifices."}

{"id": "e874f1d9-ae76-447c-85df-12e7a77d8202", "value": "A tall, thin pillar of wood, stone or metal on which a lamp could be fixed."}
{"id": "8bfc7791-842e-4e17-8ebb-d4db07831d8d", "value": "A wooden cylinder or dowel used for pinning planks or timbers together."}
{"id": "4d7781e4-255b-4939-ab7b-01654eccafe1", "value": "An associated group of toilet articles."}
{"id": "02b0e581-9b4a-4f2f-813c-013c3483ead4", "value": "An object used with cosmetics."}

{"id": "df66234e-1236-449d-8325-bb7b4525d81f", "value": "A thin flat slab used to mix cosmetics on."}
{"id": "3ca89a48-7cf1-4139-b206-2b171e6ea8cd", "value": "A heavy chain, usually of gold, worn as insignia of office or a mark of fealty or other association from the Middle Ages onwards."}
{"id": "87aee1f1-2013-479c-99da-628615df39b5", "value": "A farrier's tool for paring a horse's hoof."}
{"id": "9be3213a-38da-4941-a473-dbc4f79af5fc", "value": "A stone tool, often only polished on the edge."}
{"id": "d3703620-b60c-4c44-87d0-5bd5fd459ba4", "value": "A bit for an auger to scoop out material."}

{"id": "fabd1d90-66c2-4893-b8a3-381948a5cc54", "value": "A vessel to contain wine or water used in the Eucharist."}
{"id": "a571d87d-6ef1-4f99-8ac0-6e5df68691e3", "value": "One or more ropes or straps attached to an animal's head to provide guidance and control."}
{"id": "e137c66e-c997-40bd-9d86-f5387ffebe7d", "value": "A sample taken from waterlogged conditions."}

{"id": "133dd515-664e-4427-8883-bd709ffd6858", "value": "An object designed to add curls into hair."}

{"id": "48d7854d-6c51-45ef-8ca3-3de850625197", "value": "A bone or antler point with rows of barbs, usually on one side only."}

{"id": "2fc59bcb-3727-4fe5-af6f-bd7410119547", "value": "Thinner and narrower than a horse shoe these are also rarer as donkeys tend to be shod less often than horses."}
{"id": "dcaa61cf-aa07-4791-8451-581a671747ef", "value": "An object to point at words whilst reading, eg the Alfred jewel."}

{"id": "e15923a3-b9af-4a74-8149-5921abcd2e4d", "value": "A light covering for the foot, usually worn indoors."}

{"id": "8d7b6b8c-2db4-4608-b7d9-c8796319852a", "value": "Type of footwear which covers a minimum of the foot and ankle."}
{"id": "b672a0a5-fff5-4466-9fe9-1de4251d85fb", "value": "A box used for divination."}

{"id": "503713c3-c299-435f-a8af-2f2c13ef21ee", "value": "A covering for the leg which fits closely."}
{"id": "57032858-27d5-469a-93bd-cad40a061ab9", "value": "A container for incense."}

{"id": "c445a083-a2cd-4ebb-b5a2-97aaf5a30a4a", "value": "A bow, fixed to a stock, with a mechanism to fire the bow."}
{"id": "e08e1a31-6925-47b0-b4ce-c21e1e5a48d0", "value": "Any non structural fitting on a vehicle."}
